	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Ok, first off I'm gonna need to know how NES calculates values to place them in effect, especially for moving things.
<br />
<br />Game maker's movement runs by a variable called "speed".
<br />
<br />1 speed = 1 pixel movement per step/frame/clock cycle.
<br />Mario's walk speed is like 18, but I know he doesn't move at 18 pixels per frame.
<br />
<br />I need to kinda pick up on how or where in the ASM does it apply this value into mario's speed.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

